in.tamchow.fractal.misc.bs

Class BrainSext

  • java.lang.Object
    • in.tamchow.fractal.misc.bs.BrainSext

  • public class BrainSext
extends java.lang.Object
    Interpreter for custom BF-family language christened "BrainSext"(raw pun and acronym for "Brains Extended", capable of interpreting PBrain, BrainFlow, pure BF (directly), equivalent command sets from Extended BF,and a set of extended behaviour from PointerLang here (with replacement by equivalent or extended command codes)

    Example "Hello World" program: 

    [G2.]\Hello World
    Explanation: 1. Anything after '\', or halt, is preloaded as data 2. '[' indicates start of loop 3. 'G' will execute next operation if value at pointer is greater than value in storage, which is by default -1; 4. 2 is the index in the code string relative to the currently executing operand to jump to, if the condition ('G') is not met. 5. '.' outputs the character representation of the value at the pointer 6. ']' indicates end of loop
